        <title>PPT.MSGPAYMENTTYPE</title>
        <table>PPT.MSGPAYMENTTYPE</table>
    </header>
    <overview>
        <ovdesc>
            <p>This screen is used to define different message payment types in the payments hub.</p>
            <p>A record authorised in this screen will create or amend or reverse a record in store table, PPT.MSGPAYMENTTYPE</p>
        </ovdesc>
    </overview>
    <menu>
                <t>
            <field>ID</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Unique identifier for Message Payment Type enttity.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>i) 35 Alphanumeric characters.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>MessagePaymentType</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Indicates the name of the message payment type.</p>
                <p/>
                <p>Examples:</p>
                <p>101 - Request for Transfer – SWIFT MT</p>
                <p>103 - Customer Credit Transfer –SWIFT MT</p>
                <p>202 - Bank Transfer – SWIFT</p>
                <p>BACSCT - BACS Credit Transfer</p>
                <p>BACSDD - BACS Direct Debit</p>
                <p>HKCLGCD - HKICL Cheques debit</p>
                <p>OT33 - Standing Order - Outward Faster Payment.</p>
                <p>OT06 - Standing Order - Outward CHAPS payment.</p>
                <p>SAL - Salary Batch</p>
                <p>NOR - Normal (non-salary) Batch</p>
                <p>BACSCC - BACS Cheques Credit</p>
                <p>BACSCD - BACS Cheques Debit </p>
                <p>HKCLGCDST - HKICL Cheques debit Settlement </p>
                <p>BACSCTST - BACS Credit Transfer Settlement</p>
                <p>BACSDDST - BACS Direct Debit Settlement</p>
                <p>BACSCCST - BACS Cheques Credit Settlement</p>
                <p>BACSCDST - BACS Cheques Debit Settlement</p>
                <p>ATABE - Account to Account Transfer Belgium – Payment Router</p>
                <p>ATADE - Account to Account Transfer Germany – Payment Router</p>
                <p>ATAGB - Account to Account Transfer UK – Payment Router</p>
                <p>MT103 - Request for Transfer – Payment Router</p>
                <p>MT103-OTHER - Request for Transfer – Payment Router</p>
                <p>MT103-U-INT - Urgent Request for Transfer – Payment Router</p>
                <p/>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>Mandatory input.1-10 alphanumeric characters. </p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>MessagePaymentTypeDescription</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Description of the Payment Message Type.</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>i) 1-128 Alphanumeric characters. (Mandatory input)</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>RAC</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Record Activation Code generated for the record by the payment's hub. </p>
                <p>Possible values:</p>
                <p>N - Not active</p>
                <p>A -  Active</p>
                <p>H - History</p>
                <p>F - Future</p>
                <p>C - Not active future</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>19 alphanumeric characters.</p>
                <p>The value is not editable by the user.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>RSC</field>
            <desc>
                <p>Record Status Code generated for the record by the payments hub.</p>
                <p>Possible values:</p>
                <p>L - Live</p>
                <p>U - Unapproved</p>
                <p>R - Reversed</p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>1 alphanumeric character.</p>
                <p>The value is not editable by the user.</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
